<p>
	And despite the larger value of <m>N</m>, <m>f_N</m> does not appear to be approaching the
	square wave function.
	The difference is pronounced near the discontinuities in the function.
	This is called \emph{Gibbs Phenomena} and it can be shown in this situation that the local max
	near <m>x=0</m> in fact grows without bound as <m>N \rightarrow \infty</m>, despite the fact
	that <m>||f_N-f|| \rightarrow 0</m>.
</p>
